Hello, we're PPONG's family.
We went to Flaum, a dog-friendly camping site in Gimhae, Gyeongsangnam-do.
It was an attractive camping site with a nice pine forest path.
There were a lot of bugs, but the bathroom, shower room, and sink room were very clean.
It was nice to have a large dog park and a swimming pool available for use.
It was a camping trip in heavy rain accompanied by an unexpected lightning strike.
We had a great time eating delicious octopus.

And we went to a travel destination near the campsite.
We played a game of walking on the railroad with my family at the Jinyeong Station Railroad Museum.
Ki-ppong won and we are going to win the MacBook. ha ha ha.
We also went to a nearby homemade donut cafe with my dog.
The owner was very friendly and the donuts were really pretty and delicious.
We also went to Bongha Village.
We visited the thatched-roof house that was the birthplace of former President Roh Moo-hyun.
My parents were very happy as they looked at the cozy countryside home.

Thank you.
